# This script is intented to be used with git and bash.

0) Create a generic directory to store git-related scripts below the user home directory
$: mkdir -p $HOME/.git-custom

1) Clone the project code below the directory with git-related scripts
$: git clone https://github.com/denvazh/git-jautf8.git $HOME/.git-custom/git-jautf8

2) Add lines below to either .bashrc or .bash_profile 
 if [ -f $HOME/.git-custom/git-jautf8/init.sh ]; then
         . $HOME/.git-custom/git-jautf8/init.sh
 fi

3) Re-open terminal or just load again either .bashrc or .bash_profile:
$: source .bashrc
 or
$: source .bash_profile

For more details, please refer to the manual
$: man git-jautf8
